This is easier said than done. The more complex the gameplay loop, the more work has to be done; the more work that has to be done, the less likely it can be completed in a timely fashion in people's down-time between other commitments. That's probably why 4chan keeps going to VNs.
Having said that though, there ARE rudimentary alternatives that can have more complex gameplay loops. A massively branching CYOA, for example, an interactive fiction game, etc.
To my mind it'd have to be something where it can scale well. I remember wondering about a Bea Game where there's an element of running the DIY shop with her. This can literally just be variables, costs, profit, etc. and is as easy as pie to implement in basically any engine. Something like a point and click adventure game needs a lot of art and assets before it even gets to a proof of concept.
